Davido recently took to Twitter to reply a fan who tried to advise him on how to spend his money on social media.
The singer earlier announced on Twitter that he would be giving 20 million to 20 people with business or start up ideas on Friday. Meanwhile, a fan identified as Daniel Regha saw the post and deemed it fit to advise the popular singer on the best way to disburse the funds instead.
According to him, Davido should rather use the money to render financial assistance to people in hospitals, schools and social media platforms so that the funds will not be misused.
The tweet:
Meanwhile, Davido later saw the post and reacted to it. In a quoted tweet, davido replied back and asked the fan to do whatever he wants if he has the money.
Davido’s reply:
The singer’s response caught some people’s attention and they took to the comment section and reacted to it.
Here is a screen capture of the some reactions;
Davido is a popular and generous singer who often share funds to his fans every now and then anyway he sees fit. However, it appears some people have other ideas on how he does things.
Davido has often shown that he is not easily swayed by other people’s opinions and would do whatever he sets his mind on.


